1. Introduction

    This document demonstrates document-level annotations. The annotations at the top provide metadata about the entire document.
    
    :: note :: This annotation applies to the introduction section
    
    Annotations can also be attached to specific elements within the document, as shown above.

2. Content Section

    :: status :: draft
    
    This section has its own annotation indicating its draft status. Annotations provide a flexible way to add metadata anywhere in the document.
    
    Key features of annotations:
    - Attached to document or specific elements
    - Use double colon marker (::)
    - Support parameters for rich metadata
    - Don't interrupt content flow

